CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 15, 1955, pg. 31, reads: "First '56 Ford Sold - Edward Fullum (right), of 3416 Webster Avenue smiles confidently, as he received the keys to the first 1956 Ford to be sold in this area by Mickey Wright, top salesman at the C. Spohn, Inc., 3131 Forbes Street. By contacting Wright at the Spohn Motors, customers can save tremendous amounts that rank better than the savings at any other auto dealers in Pittsburgh area. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mickey Wright handing keys for 1956 Ford car to Edward Fullum, in front of C. Spohn Inc. Ford dealership, 3131 Forbes Avenue, Oakland
